  "image": {

\    "alt": "Prince George’s County Police are investigating the death of a man following a physical struggle early Sunday morning on College Avenue.",

\    "src": "https://d3gx1wgrn4cpnk.cloudfront.net/uploads/2019/05/2013-11-8ac14ee6ec757e35e02ff25667bfaf55-2.jpg"

  },

  "blurb": "Prince George’s County Police are investigating the death of a man following a physical struggle early Sunday morning on College Avenue.\n\nAt about 1:55 a.m., police responded to the 5100 block of College Avenue for a towing dispute, the department wrote on Twitter. Upon arrival, police found two men involved in a physical struggle and separated the men, the posts read.\n\nOne of the men was unresponsive and taken to a local hospital where he was pronounced dead. The other man was taken in for questioning, according to the department’s Twitter feed.\n\nWhen reached for comment Sunday morning, a PGPD spokesperson said the department could not provide any additional information.\n\n\_This story will be updated.\_"

